at is a CSS Gradient?"}],["$","p","6",{"className":"text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3","children":["A CSS gradient is a function that generates a smooth transition between two or more colours. Because gradients are CSS-generated rather than image-based, they are:"]}],["$","ul","10",{"className":"list-disc list-inside space-y-1 my-3 text-gray-600 text-sm","children":[["$","li","0",{"children":["Infinitely scalable (perfect for Retina displays)"]}],["$","li","1",{"children":["Load instantly (no HTTP request)"]}],["$","li","2",{"children":["Easily animated or changed dynamically with JavaScript"]}]]}],["$","p","11",{"className":"text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3","children":["CSS supports four gradient types:"]}],["$","p","12",{"className":"text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3","children":["1. ",["$","code","1",{"className":"bg-gray-100 text-red-600 px-1 rounded text-[0.85em] font-mono","children":"linear-gradient()"}]," — along a straight line"]}],["$","p","13",{"className":"text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3","children":["2. ",["$","code","1",{"className":"bg-gray-100 text-red-600 px-1 rounded text-[0.85em] font-mono","children":"radial-gradient()"}]," — radiating from a point"]}],["$","p","14",{"className":"text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3","children":["3. ",["$","code","1",{"className":"bg-gray-100 text-red-600 px-1 rounded text-[0.85em] font-mono","children":"conic-gradient()"}]," — rotating around a point"]}],["$","p","15",{"className":"text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3","children":["4. Repeating variants of each for tiled patterns"]}],["$","p","17",{"className":"text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3","children":["All gradients are used as values for the ",["$","code","1",{"className":"bg-gray-100 text-red-600 px-1 rounded text-[0.85em] font-mono","children":"background"}]," or ",["$","code","3",{"className":"bg-gray-100 text-red-600 px-1 rounded text-[0.85em] font-mono","children":"background-image"}]," CSS property."]}],["$","h2","19",{"className":"text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-3","children":"Linear Gradients"}],["$","div","mid-ad-19",{"className":"my-6","children":["$","$L5",null,{"slot":"3333333333","format":"rectangle"}]}],["$","p","21",{"className":"text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3","children":["The most common gradient type. A linear gradient transitions colours along a straight line."]}],["$","pre","36",{"className":"bg-gray-900 text-green-300 rounded-xl p-4 overflow-x-auto text-xs font-mono my-4 whitespace-pre","children":"/* Using direction keywords */\nbackground: linear-gradient(to right, #3b82f6, #8b5cf6);\nbackground: linear-gradient(to bottom right, #10b981, #3b82f6);\n\n/* Using angles (0deg = bottom to top, 90deg = left to right) */\nbackground: linear-gradient(135deg, #f97316, #ec4899);\n\n/* Multiple colour stops */\nbackground: linear-gradient(to right, #f97316, #ec4899, #8b5cf6);\n\n/* Hard colour stop (no transition) */\nbackground: linear-gradient(to right, #3b82f6 50%, #8b5cf6 50%);"}],["$","p","38",{"className":"text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"children":"Transparency in gradients"}],": Avoid using the ",["$","code","3",{"className":"bg-gray-100 text-red-600 px-1 rounded text-[0.85em] font-mono","children":"transparent"}]," keyword — it fades through black. Use ",["$","code","5",{"className":"bg-gray-100 text-red-600 px-1 rounded text-[0.85em] font-mono","children":"rgba(r,g,b,0)"}]," instead:"]}],["$","pre","43",{"className":"bg-gray-900 text-green-300 rounded-xl p-4 overflow-x-auto text-xs font-mono my-4 whitespace-pre","children":"/* Correct fade to transparent */\nbackground: linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(0,0,0,0.8), rgba(0,0,0,0));"}],["$","p","45",{"className":"text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3","children":["For the right hex colour values to use in your gradients, see our [Hex to RGB guide](/blog/hex-color-guide) or use our [Hex to RGB Converter](/tools/hex-to-rgb)."]}],["$","h2","47",{"className":"text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-3","children":"Radial Gradients"}],["$","p","49",{"className":"text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3","children":["Radial gradients radiate outward from a central point, creating circular or elliptical patterns. Ideal for spotlight effects, button highlights, and organic-looking colour transitions."]}],["$","pre","61",{"className":"bg-gray-900 text-green-300 rounded-xl p-4 overflow-x-auto text-xs font-mono my-4 whitespace-pre","children":"/* Basic circle */\nbackground: radial-gradient(circle, #f97316, #8b5cf6);\n\n/* Positioned centre */\nbackground: radial-gradient(circle at top left, #3b82f6, #1e293b);\nbackground: radial-gradient(circle at 30% 70%, #ec4899, #1e293b);\n\n/* Fade to transparent */\nbackground: radial-gradient(circle at center, #f97316 0%, transparent 70%);"}],["$","p","63",{"className":"text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3","children":["Common use cases: spotlight overlays on hero images, soft background glows behind UI cards, vintage vignette effects, and radial menu highlight states."]}],["$","h2","65",{"className":"text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-3","children":"Conic Gradients"}],["$","p","67",{"className":"text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3","children":["Conic gradients rotate colours around a central point, like a colour wheel or pie chart."]}],["$","pre","87",{"className":"bg-gray-900 text-green-300 rounded-xl p-4 overflow-x-auto text-xs font-mono my-4 whitespace-pre","children":"/* Basic conic gradient (starts at top, goes clockwise) */\nbackground: conic-gradient(red, yellow, green, blue, red);\n\n/* Colour wheel */\nbackground: conic-gradient(\n  hsl(0, 100%, 50%),\n  hsl(90, 100%, 50%),\n  hsl(180, 100%, 50%),\n  hsl(270, 100%, 50%),\n  hsl(360, 100%, 50%)\n);\n\n/* Pie chart effect with hard stops */\nbackground: conic-gradient(#3b82f6 40%, #ec4899 40% 65%, #10b981 65%);\n\n/* Custom starting angle */\nbackground: conic-gradient(from 45deg, red, yellow, green);"}],["$","h2","89",{"className":"text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-3","children":"Repeating Gradients"}],["$","p","91",{"className":"text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3","children":["Repeating gradients tile their pattern across the element, creating geometric patterns and textures."]}],["$","pre","111",{"className":"bg-gray-900 text-green-300 rounded-xl p-4 overflow-x-auto text-xs font-mono my-4 whitespace-pre","children":"/* Diagonal stripes */\nbackground: repeating-linear-gradient(\n  45deg,\n  #1e293b 0px,\n  #1e293b 10px,\n  #334155 10px,\n  #334155 20px\n);\n\n/* Concentric circles */\nbackground: repeating-radial-gradient(\n  circle,\n  transparent 0,\n  transparent 20px,\n  rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.3) 20px,\n  rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.3) 22px\n);"}],["$","h2","113",{"className":"text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-3","children":"Layering Multiple Gradients"}],["$","p","115",{"className":"text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3","children":["CSS backgrounds can be layered — you can combine multiple gradients. Later layers appear below earlier layers."]}],["$","pre","128",{"className":"bg-gray-900 text-green-300 rounded-xl p-4 overflow-x-auto text-xs font-mono my-4 whitespace-pre","children":"/* Gradient overlay on a gradient background */\nbackground:\n  linear-gradient(rgba(0,0,0,0.4), rgba(0,0,0,0.4)),\n  linear-gradient(135deg, #f97316, #8b5cf6);\n\n/* Mesh gradient effect */\nbackground:\n  radial-gradient(circle at 20% 30%, rgba(59,130,246,0.15) 0%, transparent 50%),\n  radial-gradient(circle at 80% 70%, rgba(236,72,153,0.15) 0%, transparent 50%),\n  #0f172a;"}],["$","h2","130",{"className":"text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-3","children":"Practical Design Examples"}],["$","p","132",{"className":"text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"children":"Subtle background for cards:"}],""]}],["$","pre","138",{"className":"bg-gray-900 text-green-300 rounded-xl p-4 overflow-x-auto text-xs font-mono my-4 whitespace-pre","children":".card {\n  background: linear-gradient(135deg, #ffffff 0%, #f0fdf4 100%);\n  border: 1px solid #d1fae5;\n}"}],["$","p","140",{"className":"text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"children":"Gradient text (Webkit required):"}],""]}],["$","pre","148",{"className":"bg-gray-900 text-green-300 rounded-xl p-4 overflow-x-auto text-xs font-mono my-4 whitespace-pre","children":".gradient-text {\n  background: linear-gradient(135deg, #f97316, #ec4899);\n  -webkit-background-clip: text;\n  -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;\n  background-clip: text;\n}"}],["$","p","150",{"className":"text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"children":"Hero section background:"}],""]}],["$","pre","158",{"className":"bg-gray-900 text-green-300 rounded-xl p-4 overflow-x-auto text-xs font-mono my-4 whitespace-pre","children":".hero {\n  background:\n    linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.1) 0%, transparent 50%),\n    linear-gradient(225deg, rgba(236, 72, 153, 0.1) 0%, transparent 50%),\n    #ffffff;\n}"}],["$","p","160",{"className":"text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3","children":["Generate and customise these patterns visually with our [CSS Gradient Generator](/tools/css-gradient)."]}],["$","h2","162",{"className":"text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-3","children":"Animating Gradients"}],["$","p","164",{"className":"text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3","children":["CSS gradients cannot be directly transitioned or animated because they are not a single value type. However, you can animate gradients indirectly using:"]}],["$","ul","170",{"className":"list-disc list-inside space-y-1 my-3 text-gray-600 text-sm","children":[["$","li","0",{"children":["CSS custom properties with ",["$","code","1",{"className":"bg-gray-100 text-red-600 px-1 rounded text-[0.85em] font-mono","children":"@property"}]," (Chrome/Edge and now all modern browsers)"]}],["$","li","1",{"children":["",["$","code","1",{"className":"bg-gray-100 text-red-600 px-1 rounded text-[0.85em] font-mono","children":"background-position"}]," on large gradient backgrounds to create movement"]}],["$","li","2",{"children":["",["$","code","1",{"className":"bg-gray-100 text-red-600 px-1 rounded text-[0.85em] font-mono","children":"opacity"}]," transitions between layered gradient elements"]}],["$","li","3",{"children":["JavaScript to update gradient values via CSS custom properties"]}]]}],["$","p","171",{"className":"text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3","children":["The ",["$","code","1",{"className":"bg-gray-100 text-red-600 px-1 rounded text-[0.85em] font-mono","children":"@property"}]," approach enables smooth, performant gradient animations entirely in CSS."]}],["$","h2","173",{"className":"text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-3","children":"Browser Support"}],["$","p","175",{"className":"text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3","children":["All four gradient types have excellent modern browser support (98%+ globally). The ",["$","code","1",{"className":"bg-gray-100 text-red-600 px-1 rounded text-[0.85em] font-mono","children":"conic-gradient()"}]," function is now fully supported in all major browsers. There is no need for vendor prefixes in new code targeting modern browsers."]}],["$","h2","177",{"className":"text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-3","children":"Performance Tips"}],["$","p","179",{"className":"text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3","children":["Gradients are generally very performant since they are rendered by the GPU. However, very complex gradients with many stops or layered gradients applied to many elements can impact rendering performance on lower-end devices. For animations, prefer animating via CSS custom properties rather than triggering layout recalculations."]}],["$","h2","181",{"className":"text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-3","children":"Frequently Asked Questions"}],["$","p","183",{"className":"text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"children":"Q: How do I create a gradient that fades to transparent?"}],""]}],["$","p","184",{"className":"text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3","children":["Use ",["$","code","1",{"className":"bg-gray-100 text-red-600 px-1 rounded text-[0.85em] font-mono","children":"rgba(r, g, b, 0)"}]," instead of the ",["$","code","3",{"className":"bg-gray-100 text-red-600 px-1 rounded text-[0.85em] font-mono","children":"transparent"}]," keyword. For example: ",["$","code","5",{"className":"bg-gray-100 text-red-600 px-1 rounded text-[0.85em] font-mono","children":"linear-gradient(to bottom, #3b82f6, rgba(59, 130, 246, 0))"}],". The ",["$","code","7",{"className":"bg-gray-100 text-red-600 px-1 rounded text-[0.85em] font-mono","children":"transparent"}]," keyword is equivalent to ",["$","code","9",{"className":"bg-gray-100 text-red-600 px-1 rounded text-[0.85em] font-mono","children":"rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)"}]," and causes an ugly dark fade when used with coloured gradients."]}],["$","p","186",{"className":"text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"children":"Q: Can I animate a CSS gradient?"}],""]}],["$","p","187",{"className":"text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3","children":["Not directly — CSS cannot interpolate between gradient values. Workarounds include: using ",["$","code","1",{"className":"bg-gray-100 text-red-600 px-1 rounded text-[0.85em] font-mono","children":"@property"}]," to define a custom animated property, animating ",["$","code","3",{"className":"bg-gray-100 text-red-600 px-1 rounded text-[0.85em] font-mono","children":"background-position"}]," on a large gradient, or using JavaScript to update CSS custom properties."]}],["$","p","189",{"className":"text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"children":"Q: What is the difference between a radial and a conic gradient?"}],""]}],["$","p","190",{"className"